description: From Medieval Latin bombināre, present active infinitive of bombinō (“buzz, hum”), variant of Latin bombilō, from Ancient Greek βομβυλιάζειν (bombuliázein), from βόμβος (bómbos, “booming, humming”), of imitatory origin.

verbs.description: bombinate (third-person singular simple present bombinates, present participle bombinating, simple past and past participle bombinated)

entries.meaning: to buzz or hum; to speak idly, vacuously, or to little effect.
